<assessment id="u3_m1_rules2_tutor1">
   <title>Tutor</title>
   <page>
   <question id="q1">
      <body>
         <p>What is the probability that a patient taking this drug will not experience insomnia?</p>
      </body>
      <multiple_choice shuffle="false">
         <choice value="Res1">0.14</choice>
         <choice value="Res2">0.86</choice>
         <choice value="Res3">0.74</choice>
         <choice value="Res4">0.26</choice>
      </multiple_choice>
      <part>
         <response match="Res1" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect.  Note that 0.14 is P(I), and you are asked to find P(not I). </feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res2" score="10">
            <feedback>Correct. Indeed, using the complement rule, P(not I) = 1 - P(I) = 1 - 0.14 =
                  0.86.</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res3" score="0">
            <feedback>This is not quite
                  right.<?oxy_comment_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101130T155828-0500" comment="change correct?"?>
                  0.74 is<?oxy_comment_end?> the probability that a patient does not experience
                  headaches, P(not H), and you are asked to find P(not I).</feedback>
         </response>
         <response match="Res4" score="0">
            <feedback>Incorrect. 0.26 is the probability that a patient experiences headaches, P(H), and you are asked to find P(not I).</feedback>
         </response>
      </part>
   </question></page>
</assessment>
